description:
&lt;p&gt;The Princess of Wales Hospital Critical Care Unit (ITU/HDU) is looking for motivated and enthusiastic Registered Nurses who are able to demonstrate evidence based practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to work as part of a friendly and dedicated team? Then this fantastic opportunity has arisen for experienced nurses who are patient focused and who wish to develop and enhance their skills within a clinical environment that is conducive to learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a wide range of in-house training programmes as well as opportunities to further academic studies at local universities the Critical Care Unit (ITU and HDU) will help you provide a high standard of research based care. The All Wales Critical Care Competencies are used to support your learning and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be a registered nurse with ideally experience in a critical care setting. All posts will involve shift working with internal rotation from days to nights over a 12 hour shift pattern with weekend and bank holiday working as required. The posts will be based at the Princess of Wales Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda Jackson - Matron Critical Care Services - via email on Amanda.Jackson@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sophie Jones - Senior Sister Critical Care Services - 01656 752381&lt;/p&gt;
